// ==/UserScript==
//
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// WHAT THIS IS
//   A small "Organize Posts" button is added to the bottom-right of any
//   patreon.com page. Click it and the script asks Patreon (using YOUR logged-in
//   session, just like the site's own "Load more posts") for the full list of a
//   creator's posts, groups them BY MONTH, and lets you flip through them a page
//   at a time (10/20/50 per page). Only the page you're viewing is rendered, so a
//   huge archive no longer has to load all at once.
//
// HOW TO INSTALL (one time, per patron)
//   1. Install the Tampermonkey (or Violentmonkey) browser extension.
//   2. Open it → "Create a new script" → paste this whole file → Save.
//      (Or just open this .user.js file in the browser and confirm the install.)
//   3. Go to the creator's Patreon page (e.g. https://www.patreon.com/cw/Anzu777)
//      while LOGGED IN, and click the "📚 Organize Posts" button.
//
// NOTES / LIMITS (honest)
//   • You must be LOGGED IN and on a real www.patreon.com page (not an embed).
//   • It can LIST every post, but it can only open paid posts your pledge covers.
//   • It uses Patreon's internal (undocumented) API — if Patreon redesigns their
//     site, post-fetch may break; the script tries 5 ways to find the creator and
//     will ask you to paste an ID as a last resort.
//   • This is a personal-organization helper over content you already have access
//     to. It does not download, bypass payment, or expose anything you can't
//     already see.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

